      body: {
        en: `- **Run many, not one**: [the portfolio of edges](item:portfolio-of-edges) — a single pair can have its cointegration break and bleed without bound, so the mature application is a diversified, market-neutral *book* of many imperfectly-correlated spreads. Diversifying across edges is exactly what keeps a broken pair from ending you, and it is the same mean-variance logic that turns a handful of thin edges into a tradeable Sharpe.
- **Is the spread real or mined?**: [backtest overfitting and the deflated Sharpe](item:backtest-overfitting-dsr) — scan thousands of tickers and you *will* find spuriously "cointegrated" pairs that are pure in-sample coincidence. The statistics that catch real cointegration produce false positives at scale, so you must demand an economic rationale and deflate your in-sample stats for the number of pairs you searched.
- **A cousin of cointegration arbitrage**: [Makarov & Schoar's cross-exchange / cross-country price gaps](item:makarov-schoar-2020) — the same family of "two prices for one economic thing should converge" logic, here Bitcoin trading at different prices across exchanges and countries, with the persistence of the gap revealing the *limits of arbitrage* (capital controls, transfer frictions) that also explain why pairs spreads do not close instantly.
- **Size for the break, not the average**: [trading via expectancy and survival](item:traderxo-expectancy) — a left-tail-exposed strategy (the broken-cointegration slope) can show a beautiful Sharpe and 100% recent win rate and still ruin you on one trade, so the discipline is to size positions for the bad tail and survive the path, exactly as in the expectancy framework.`,
        id: `- **Jalanin banyak, bukan satu**: [portofolio edge](item:portfolio-of-edges) — satu pair bisa cointegration-nya patah dan berdarah tanpa batas, jadi aplikasi matang-nya itu *buku* banyak spread berkorelasi-tak-sempurna yang terdiversifikasi, market-neutral. Mendiversifikasi lintas edge itu persis yang ngejaga pair patah dari ngabisin kamu, dan itu logika mean-variance yang sama yang ngubah segenggam edge tipis jadi Sharpe yang bisa-ditradingkan.
- **Spread-nya nyata atau ditambang?**: [backtest overfitting dan deflated Sharpe](item:backtest-overfitting-dsr) — pindai ribuan ticker dan kamu *bakal* nemu pair "cointegrated" palsu yang murni kebetulan in-sample. Statistik yang nangkep cointegration nyata ngehasilin positif palsu pada skala, jadi kamu harus nuntut rasional ekonomi dan ndeflasi statistik in-sample-mu buat jumlah pair yang kamu cari.
- **Sepupu arbitrase cointegration**: [celah harga lintas-bursa / lintas-negara Makarov & Schoar](item:makarov-schoar-2020) — keluarga logika "dua harga buat satu hal ekonomi mestinya konvergen" yang sama, di sini Bitcoin diperdagangkan di harga berbeda lintas bursa dan negara, dengan persistensi celahnya nyingkapin *limit arbitrase* (kontrol modal, friksi transfer) yang juga ngejelasin kenapa spread pairs gak nutup seketika.
- **Size buat patahan, bukan rata-rata**: [trading lewat expectancy dan kelangsungan-hidup](item:traderxo-expectancy) — strategi yang terekspos ekor-kiri (lereng cointegration-patah) bisa nunjukin Sharpe cantik dan win rate 100% baru-baru ini dan masih ngancurin kamu di satu trade, jadi disiplin-nya itu size posisi buat ekor buruk dan bertahan di jalur, persis kayak di framework expectancy.`
      }
